Layer  Explanation
raw layer
store sourse data exactly as received

Purpose:
. Preserve original files
. support audit and troubshooting
. Allow reprocessing if business rules change

Recommendation format 
. CSV for source file export 
. Json for API or event data
. Keep the orignal source format

# Bronze layer
stores ingestion data with light technial cleanup
typical change
. Add ingestion timestamp
. add source file name 
. convert raw files into delta or parquet

# Silver layer
Store cleaned and standardized data

typical change
. Remove duplicates
. fix data type
. handle nulls 
. join related dataset
. apply basic business rules

Gold layer
store Business-ready dataset for reporting and analytics

Example: gold /ecommerce/daily_summary
 typical change
. data analytics
. Power bi devlopers
. business stakeholders

PIPELINE FLOW :-

1.Source system
2. ADF or fabric data factory ingestion
3. ADLS row layer
4. databricks/pyspark conversion to bronze
5. Cleaning and join into silver
6. Aggregation and KPIs into gold
7. Power bi /analytics consumption

Partitioning strategy:
Load_year/load_month/load_day

reason:
tracks when data arrived
makes daily reload easier
help with audit and Trabulshooting

Silver and gold layers:
business_date, order_date,event_date or report_month

Access control design:
Row: Data eng and platform admin can have access
Bronze: Data eng
silver: data eng anf selected analytsis
gold: Analytst , BI developer and approved bsuiness user


Interview Notes:
1. Why do we separate raw, bronze, silver, and gold?
We separate layers to organize data by quality and purpose. Raw stores original data, 
bronze stores ingested data, silver stores cleaned data, and gold stores business-ready data for reporting.

